         <div xml:lang="en" type="translation">
            <ab>Lampon, son of Ammonius, manager of the house of the gymnasiarchs of Oxyrynchos, to the collectors of the corn revenue of the middle toparchy at Petne, greeting. Pay from the past 19th year's store of wheat belonging to the gymnasiarchs and deposited with you, sixty artabae, 60 art., to Sarapion, son of Heliodorus, late exegetes at Oxyrynchos. The 20th year of Aurelius Antonius Caesar and Aurelius Commodius Caesar our sovereigns, Athyr 3. (Grenfell &amp; Hunt)</ab>
